Below is a **wireframe pack in Markdown** for the **10 core screens**. It’s written like a build spec: **layout + components + fields + default copy + error states + AU-safe disclaimers**.

You can paste this into `product/wireframes_v1.md`.

---

```md
# Advyser V1 Wireframe Pack (AU) — 10 Core Screens
Scope: AU marketplace for financial + property-related advisors.
Principles: consumer browsing is low-friction; advisor value comes from leads + dashboard; AI is supply-side, advisor-only.

---

## Global UI Patterns

### Header (Public)
- Logo (left)
- Nav: Find an Advisor | For Advisors | About | Login
- CTA button: "Find an Advisor"

### Header (Logged-in Consumer)
- Nav: Search | My Requests | Messages
- Profile dropdown

### Header (Logged-in Advisor)
- Nav: Leads | Messages | Clients | Copilot | Profile
- CTA: "Create Copilot Run" (optional quick action)

### Footer (All Public Pages)
- Disclaimer (AU-safe):
  - "Advyser connects Australians with financial and property professionals. Information on this site is general and not personal advice. Consider your circumstances and speak with a licensed professional."
- Links: Privacy | Terms | Contact | Report a listing

### Badges
- Verified (Basic)
- Licence Verified
- Fast Responder
- Taking New Clients

### Status Chips (Leads)
- New
- Contacted
- Booked
- Converted
- Declined
- Closed

---

# Screen 1 — Home (Marketplace Landing)

## Goal
Help users find advisors quickly by type + location.

## Layout (Desktop)
[Header]
Hero:
- H1: "Find the right financial or property advisor in Australia"
- Subtext: "Search verified professionals. Send a request. Book when you're ready."
Search Module:
- Field: Advisor Type (dropdown)
- Field: Location (suburb/postcode)
- Field: Radius (dropdown, default 25km)
- Button: "Search"
Secondary:
- Category tiles (4):
  - Financial Advisers
  - Mortgage Brokers
  - Buyer’s Agents
  - Property Advisors
Trust row:
- "Verified businesses"
- "Secure messaging"
- "No-cost to browse"
[Footer]

## Fields
- Advisor Type (required)
- Location (required)
- Radius (optional)

## Microcopy
- Location placeholder: "e.g., 3000, Sydney, Parramatta"
- Helper text: "Online advisors can work Australia-wide."

## Error States
- Missing location → "Enter a suburb or postcode."
- Invalid location → "We couldn't find that location. Try a nearby suburb or postcode."

---

# Screen 2 — Search Results

## Goal
Let users filter and compare advisors; default sort is "Recommended".

## Layout
[Header]
Top bar:
- Breadcrumb: Home > Search
- Summary line: "Mortgage Brokers near Richmond VIC (25km) — 42 results"
Left rail (filters) / mobile filter drawer:
Results list (cards) + pagination/infinite scroll

### Filter panel (V1)
- Advisor Type (multi-select)
- Service Mode:
  - Toggle pills: Online / In-person
- Specialty (multi-select)
- Fee Model (multi-select):
  - Hourly / Fixed / Ongoing / % / Not listed
- Verified only (toggle)
- Taking new clients (toggle)
- Availability (toggle): "Openings in next 7 days" (optional if you have data)
- Language (multi-select)

### Sort dropdown
- Recommended (default)
- Nearest (if in-person)
- Highest rated
- Soonest availability

## Result Card (each listing)
Left: avatar/logo
Main:
- Name / Business
- Badges: Verified/Licence Verified/Fast Responder
- Type: "Mortgage Broker"
- Location: "Richmond VIC" + distance if in-person
- Top specialties (max 3)
- Price indicator: "From $X" or "Pricing not listed"
- Snippet: 1–2 lines from headline/bio
Right:
- CTA: "View profile"
- Secondary: "Request intro"

## Explainability (small text)
- "Recommended because: Verified + specialises in first home buyers"
(Use 1 reason max.)

## Empty state
- "No results match your filters."
- CTA: "Clear filters" | "Expand radius"

---

# Screen 3 — Advisor Profile (Listing Page)

## Goal
Build trust + convert to Request Intro.

## Layout
[Header]
Hero section:
- Name / Business
- Type (e.g., Financial Adviser)
- Badges row
- Location + service mode
- Primary CTA: "Request intro"
- Secondary CTA: "Message" (only after login)
Tabs:
- Overview | Services & Pricing | Credentials | Reviews

### Overview tab
- "Who I help" (bullets)
- "What we do" (short paragraphs)
- Specialties (tags)
- Service areas (map snippet / list)
- Meeting modes (online/in-person)
- Languages

### Services & Pricing tab
- Service offering cards (e.g., "Initial consult", "Ongoing service")
- Pricing text (freeform)
- What’s included (bullets)

### Credentials tab
- "Licence / Registration"
- Rows:
  - Type, Number, State, Verified status, Verified date
- Microcopy:
  - "Verified on YYYY-MM-DD. Source: Register / Documentation."

### Reviews tab
- Rating summary
- Review list (verified engagements only)
- "How reviews work" tooltip:
  - "Reviews are only from users who contacted an advisor through Advyser."

## AU-safe disclaimer block (on page)
- "Advyser does not provide financial or property advice. Always consider your circumstances and consult a licensed professional."

## Error states
- Listing inactive → show: "This listing is currently unavailable."

---

# Screen 4 — Request Intro (Lead Form)

## Goal
Collect a clean client brief without giving advice.

## Layout
[Header]
Title: "Request an introduction"
Subtext: "Answer a few questions so the advisor can respond with next steps."

Form sections:

### A) What you need help with
- Dropdown: Primary goal (required)
  - Examples by type:
    - Financial: "Retirement planning", "Investment planning", "Debt reduction"
    - Mortgage: "First home loan", "Refinance", "Investment loan"
    - Buyer’s agent: "Find & negotiate a property", "Auction bidding"
- Multi-select: Specialties (optional)

### B) Your situation (free text)
- Textarea (required): "Describe your situation and what you want to achieve"
- Helper: "Avoid sharing sensitive IDs like TFN. You can share documents later if needed."

### C) Logistics
- Preferred meeting mode: Online / In-person / Either
- Location (auto-filled from search; editable)
- Timeline (dropdown): "ASAP / 1–3 months / 3–6 months / Flexible"
- Budget range (optional, ranges only)
- Upload documents (optional)
  - Allowed: pdf/docx/jpg/png
  - Microcopy: "Only upload documents you’re comfortable sharing."

### D) Consent
- Checkbox (required):
  - "I understand Advyser connects me with an advisor and does not provide personal advice."

Buttons:
- Primary: "Send request"
- Secondary: "Save draft" (optional)

## Validation
- Must have goal + situation + consent
- Errors:
  - "Please describe your situation."
  - "You must accept the consent to continue."

## Success screen (inline after submit)
- "Request sent"
- Next steps:
  - "The advisor will reply here in Messages."
  - CTA: "Go to My Requests"

---

# Screen 5 — Sign up / Login

## Goal
Fast authentication with minimal friction.

## Layout
[Header]
Card:
Tabs: Sign up | Login

### Sign up
- Email (required)
- Password (required)
- Phone (optional but recommended)
- Checkbox: Terms + Privacy
Button: "Create account"

### Login
- Email
- Password
- Button: "Login"
- Link: "Forgot password"

## Copy
- "We’ll only use your details to manage your requests and messages."

## Errors
- Invalid credentials → "Email or password incorrect."
- Unverified email → "Check your email to verify your account."

---

# Screen 6 — Consumer Dashboard (My Requests)

## Goal
Consumer sees all requests, statuses, and messages.

## Layout
[Header logged-in consumer]
Tabs: My Requests | Messages | Settings

### My Requests list
Table/cards:
- Advisor/Business name
- Type
- Status chip
- Last updated
- CTA: "View" opens request detail

Empty state:
- "No requests yet."
- CTA: "Search advisors"

### Request detail view (subpage/modal)
- Summary of the request (what user submitted)
- Status timeline
- Messages panel
- Attachments
- CTA: "Send message"

---

# Screen 7 — Claim Business / Join (Advisor)

## Goal
Let a real advisor claim an existing listing or create a new one.

## Layout
[Header public or advisor]
Title: "Claim your business on Advyser"
Options:
- Search business name field (typeahead)
- OR "My business isn’t listed" → create business flow (simple)

### Claim form
Section 1: Your details
- Full name
- Role (Owner/Principal, Staff)
- Work email
- Phone (OTP verification)

Section 2: Business verification
Pick ONE proof-of-control:
- OTP to business phone (if matches listing)
- Verify email domain (send link)
- Website verification code (copy/paste snippet)

Section 3: Credentials (guided by advisor type)
- Advisor Type (required)
- Licence/registration number(s) (optional for initial claim; required for Licence Verified badge)
- Upload evidence (optional)

Submit button: "Submit claim"

## States
- Pending review: "We’re reviewing your claim. We’ll email you when it’s approved."
- Needs more info: show requested items checklist
- Denied: "Your claim wasn’t approved" + contact support

---

# Screen 8 — Advisor Dashboard (Lead Inbox)

## Goal
Advisors manage inbound requests and convert them to clients.

## Layout
[Header logged-in advisor]
Left: Lead pipeline list (columns or status filter)
Top stats (optional): New leads, Response time, Acceptance rate

### Lead list
Rows show:
- Client label (e.g., "Lead #1023" or name if provided)
- Goal tag
- Location
- Submitted date
- Status chip
- Last message time
- CTA: "Open"

### Quick actions on row
- Accept
- Decline
- Request more info (sends templated message)

Empty state:
- "No leads yet."
- Tips: "Complete your profile to rank higher."

---

# Screen 9 — Lead Detail (Advisor)

## Goal
Advisor sees the client brief, messages, docs, and can progress status.

## Layout
[Header]
Top bar:
- Client label + lead id
- Status dropdown
- Buttons: Accept | Decline | Mark booked | Archive

Main columns:
Left (Client Brief)
- Goal
- Situation (user text)
- Logistics (mode, timeline, location)
- Uploaded docs list
- "Missing info checklist" (manual in V1; Copilot later)

Right (Messages)
- Conversation thread
- Composer (text + attachments)
- Templates dropdown:
  - "Request documents"
  - "Next steps"
  - "Booking link"

Bottom (Internal Notes)
- Notes timeline
- "Add note" input

## Copy
- Accept action: "Accepting creates a client workspace and enables Copilot."
- Decline action: require reason (internal only):
  - "Out of scope / Not taking new clients / Location / Other"

---

# Screen 10 — Admin Console (Claims + Moderation)

## Goal
Operate trust & safety: verify claims, credentials, reviews.

## Layout
[Admin header]
Tabs:
- Claim requests
- Credentials
- Reviews
- Listings
- Reports

### Claim Requests table
Columns:
- Business
- Claimant user
- Proof-of-control method
- Status
- Submitted date
Row opens detail panel:

#### Claim detail panel
Left:
- Business profile snapshot
- ABN details (if available)
- Listing info
Right:
- Claimant details (email/phone verified)
- Evidence files
- Links to registers (manual verification shortcuts)
Actions:
- Approve (assign owner)
- Needs more info (checklist + message)
- Deny (reason + lockout toggle)

### Reviews moderation
- Review text + lead reference
- Approve / Reject / Hide

### Reports queue
- Listing report type
- Evidence
- Actions: warn, suspend listing, request more info

---

## Copy Library (Reusable)

### "AI / Advice boundary" (public)
- "Advyser connects you with professionals. We do not provide financial or property advice."

### "Verified" tooltip
- "Verified means we’ve confirmed business ownership and/or credentials. Verified on {date}."

### Lead decline message (advisor → consumer template)
- "Thanks for your request. Unfortunately we’re unable to assist at this time. You may wish to contact another advisor in your area."

### Request more info template
- "To understand your situation, could you please share: {checklist}. Once received, we can confirm next steps."
```

